metadata.name: Becoming a Woman #1/21
metadata.description: The artwork features a diverse cast of female figures facing various obstacles such as childbirth, discrimination, body image issues, and stereotypical labels. The fragmented imagery of their bodies and faces highlights the internal and external struggles they endure while also celebrating their resilience and determination. Pink and red colors express the femininity and pain of womanhood while the abstract forms symbolize the complexities of the female experience.
